 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Mon, 29 May 2006 12:58:36 +0200

grml-etc (0.7-35) unstable; urgency=low

  * The "oh, btw - zsh rocks as well" update:
  * /etc/zsh/zshrc
    - added function zsh-help which prints useful information
      regarding zsh configuration/setup/....
    - added support for 'NOMENU=1 zsh' to disable menus in zsh at all;
      thanks to Julius Plenz for 'setopt no_auto_menu'. :)
  * /etc/skel/.zshrc:
    - load compinit even though we load it in /etc/zsh/zshrc as well,
      prevents errror when using /etc/skel/.zshrc only
    - replaced $BROWSER with ${(z)BROWSER} as requested by Matthias
      so we can provide something like BROWSER="dog --links".
    - set alias la to 'ls -Al' (we don't need the . and .. directories),
      again on request by Matthias
    - source ~/.zshrc.local if file is present so people can stay in
      sync with /etc/skel/.zshrc through a symlink to ~/.zshrc

 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Sun, 28 May 2006 11:58:23 +0200

grml-etc (0.7-34) unstable; urgency=low

  * The "vim 7 rocks" update:
    - 'set hidden' in /etc/vim/vimrc as I require undo to work
      even as root with multiple buffers
    - big update of /etc/skel/.vimrc with check for version7
      and appropriate configuration and even some cool tips
    - added /etc/skel/.vim/spellfile.add so we can add our own
      words to a spelling file

 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Sun, 28 May 2006 01:20:46 +0200

grml-etc (0.7-33) unstable; urgency=low

  * Deactivated the "Prepend/append register [/] to the paste if ^a^]
    is pressed." hack in /etc/grml/screenrc.
  * Added 'autoload promptinit ; promptinit' to /etc/zsh/zshrc as
    suggested by Matthias Kopfermann.
  * Source ~/.zshrc.global if file is present. This provides the feature
    to use /etc/zsh/zshrc in your $HOME as well.
  * Added /etc/skel/.kshrc as suggested by Matthias Kopfermann, thanks!
  * Added deactivated "print $'\e[?96;0;64c'" to /etc/skel/.zshrc, cool
    feature by Matthias Kopfermann, thanks!
  * Set $WRITE_ON_UDEV in /etc/zsh/zshenv to prevent people from
    confusion when running MAKEDEV on /dev provided by udev.
  * Let's try to use single click in /etc/skel/.ideskrc as some people
    are confused when pressing double click on *nix systems.
  * Removed $CURDIR occurencies in debian/rules.

 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Sat, 27 May 2006 23:29:42 +0200

