    - make zshrc more compatible to older zsh versions

 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Sun,  9 Jan 2005 12:36:04 +0100

grml-etc (0.1-24) unstable; urgency=low

  * Removed .xpm files out of debian/conffiles.
  * Removed /etc/grml_version [adjust it in chroot].

 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Sun,  9 Jan 2005 11:06:50 +0100

grml-etc (0.1-23) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed several bugs in /etc/skel/.fluxbox.
  * Removed fluxbox-styles: Calabi, Nuevat3k-Glacier,
    Magraxx, sea and Nuevat3k-Glacier.
  * Updated /etc/grml/screenrc and /etc/skel.screenrc (changed
    static entries 'root' and 'grml' to $USER).
  * Fixed zshrc (removed setopt in precmd), otherwise
    you'll get zsh parse error when running (unreal)
    commands like:
       FOO=mika test' "$FOO" = "mika" ; echo "FOO = $FOO"

 -- Michael Prokop <mika@grml.org>  Sat,  8 Jan 2005 14:53:49 +0100

